<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-10T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-10T07:00:00-05:00" n="255" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d255">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/7–1050: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Douglas</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-10T13:00:00+01:00">July 10,
                                1950—1 p. m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received July 10—2:03 p. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>175. Eyes only for the Secretary. Re Deptel 123, July 9. Discussed with Prime
                        Minister four points suggested in reftel. He indicated complete approval but
                        asked that matter be discussed detail with Strang who at that time had been
                        sent out to see Bevin at the hospital.</p>
                    <p>Will see Strang soon as he returns.<note n="1" xml:id="d255fn1">See <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                    </p>
                    <p>Department pass Moscow. Repeated information Moscow 12, eyes only for
                        Ambassador.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>